<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-18124] Config parameter keystore_password should be nullable</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-18124</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Some SSL configuration may pass unencrypted private keys. PEMReader might accept that by assuming keyPassword to be null in that case (e.g. &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/f9e033f519c14596da4dc954875756a69aea4e78/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/security/PEMReader.java#L103&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/f9e033f519c14596da4dc954875756a69aea4e78/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/security/PEMReader.java#L103&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Current configuration reader does not accept keystore_password parameter to be set null or empty in the cassandra.yaml.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
